<chapter xml:id="fitting-models">
  <title>Fitting models to data</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This chapter introduces the concept of statistical models and how we fit them to data.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <section xml:id="what-is-a-model">
    <title>What is a model?</title>
    <p>
      A statistical model is a mathematical representation of the relationships in our data.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="fitting-models-section">
    <title>Fitting models</title>
    <p>
      We fit models to data to understand patterns and make predictions.
    </p>
  </section>
</chapter>
